packets.ccsds

Class CcsdsPkt

  • java.lang.Object
    • packets.ccsds.CcsdsPkt
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CcsdsCmdPkt, CcsdsTlmPkt

    public class CcsdsPkt
extends java.lang.Object
    FULLY DOCUMENTED. This class contains a byte array that is the packet. This class is used to perform operations on data that is in all Ccsds packets, such as determining the stream ID, sequence count, and length. Each CmdPkt and TlmPkt has an instance of CcsdsCmdPkt or CcsdsTlmPkt respectively.
    Author:
    David McComas

      • CcsdsPkt

      • CcsdsPkt

        CcsdsPkt(int StreamId,
        int Length)
        Creates a CcsdsPkt from a stream ID/Cmdmid and length. Used for command packets. Creates the byte array, and initializes everything to zero. Encodes in the byte array the stream ID, length of the command, and sequence count.
        Parameters:
        StreamId - The streamID of the command.
        Length - The entire length of the byte array.
